An additional margin of 1,000 dlrswill be required on all July 1987 delivery coffee "C" contractsas of the opening of trade Monday, March 23, the Coffee, Sugarand Cocoa Exchange, CSCE, said.    The March contract ends trading this week, making May andJuly the two "spot," or unlimited, contract months next week.    Members will then have to obtain a minimum 3,500 dlrs fornet long or net short positions in the May and July contracts,including a 2,500 original margin plus the additional 1,000 dlrspot charge. Reuter&#3;